title: Who was the most beautiful lady of the Renaissance? - Quora

response.answer_text: What is MOST beautiful to one person is not always beautiful to another.    Famed beauties: Botticelli’s Birth of Venus and Leonardo da Vinci’s Leda and the Swan (1505-10) are top answers. Do you recognize the beauty and power of women in ‘Judith Beheading Holofernes’? Artemisia Gentileschi, 1620. Uffizi Gallery. Florence. Beauty IS subjective.
